# @primer/react Usage

ALL web apps use `@primer/react` as the ONLY design system. Follow the official documentation exactly.

## Mandatory Rules

- ALWAYS use Primer components instead of raw HTML elements
- NEVER create custom components that duplicate Primer functionality
- NEVER override Primer component internals with custom CSS
- Use `ThemeProvider` at the app root — all theming via Primer tokens
- Primer components handle their own styling — use component props (`variant`, `size`, etc.)
- Layout/spacing around Primer components via SCSS Modules + Tailwind @apply (see styling-conventions rule)

## Component Mapping

| Need | Primer Component |
|------|-----------------|
| Buttons | `Button`, `IconButton` |
| Forms | `TextInput`, `Select`, `Checkbox`, `Radio`, `FormControl` |
| Layout | `PageLayout`, `SplitPageLayout` |
| Navigation | `NavList`, `UnderlineNav`, `Header` |
| Feedback | `Flash`, `Banner`, `Spinner`, `ProgressBar` |
| Overlays | `Dialog`, `ActionMenu`, `Overlay` |
| Data | `DataTable`, `Label`, `Token`, `TreeView` |
| Typography | `Heading`, `Text` |

## Atoms Wrapping Primer

Atoms wrap Primer components following the full component file structure (see component-structure rule):

```
atoms/Button/
  Button.tsx
  Button.module.scss
  Button.types.ts
  Button.utils.ts
  Button.test.tsx
  index.ts
```

```tsx
// atoms/Button/Button.types.ts
import type { ButtonProps as PrimerButtonProps } from '@primer/react'

export interface ButtonProps extends Pick<PrimerButtonProps, 'variant' | 'size' | 'disabled'> {
  label: string
  onClick: () => void
}
```

```tsx
// atoms/Button/Button.tsx
import { Button as PrimerButton } from '@primer/react'
import type { ButtonProps } from './Button.types'

export const Button = ({ label, ...rest }: ButtonProps) => (
  <PrimerButton {...rest}>{label}</PrimerButton>
)
```

